Operators and Motions 

	Commands that change text are made from an operator and a motion.

	For delete 
    		d      - is the delete operator.
    		motion - is what the operator will operate on (listed below).


Searching for help 
	:help 

	<Space> s h : to search through help

KEYMAPS I'd not like to forget 

	:yap : yank around the paragraph
	:%s/new/old/g/c : global replace 'new' with 'old' keyword
		g for global , c for query yes/no
		can be :s/new/old/g for the current line

